== Sweet iced tea

_Serves 4_

=== Ingredients

- 4 black tea bags (e.g. Lipton)
- 2 cups boiling water
- 4 cups cold water
- ½ cup sugar
- ½ lemon, sliced (optional)

=== Method

+ Steep tea bags in boiling water for 5 minutes. Don't over-steep.
+ Remove bags. Stir in sugar until dissolved.
+ Add cold water. Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Serve over ice.

---

== Grissini torinesi

_Serves 4 · ~24 breadsticks_

=== Ingredients

- 250 g bread flour or 00 flour
- 160 ml warm water
- 1 tsp instant yeast
- 1 tsp salt
- 3 tbsp olive oil
- 2 tbsp sesame seeds or rosemary (optional)

=== Method

+ Combine flour, yeast, salt. Add water and olive oil. Knead 8 minutes until smooth.
+ Cover, rest 1 hour until puffy.
+ Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C). Line two baking sheets with parchment.
+ Divide dough into 24 pieces. Roll each into a thin rope, 10--12 inches long. Sprinkle with sesame or rosemary if using.
+ Bake 18--22 minutes until golden and fully crisp, rotating halfway. Cool completely on a rack.

_Underbaked grissini go soft quickly --- when in doubt, give them 3 more minutes._

---

== Whipped ricotta

_Serves 4_

=== Ingredients

- 250 g whole-milk ricotta
- 60 g cream cheese
- 1 lemon, zested
- 1 tbsp lemon juice
- 2 tbsp olive oil
- ½ tsp salt
- 1 tsp fresh thyme or black pepper to finish

=== Method

+ Whip ricotta, cream cheese, lemon juice, and salt in a food processor or stand mixer for 2 minutes until smooth and airy.
+ Transfer to a bowl. Drizzle with olive oil, top with lemon zest and thyme or pepper. Refrigerate until serving.

_Make at least 1 hour ahead._

---

== Caprese salad with arugula

_Serves 4_

=== Ingredients

- 400 g fresh mozzarella, pre-sliced
- 4 ripe tomatoes (heirloom if possible), sliced
- 60 g arugula
- 20 fresh basil leaves
- 3 tbsp extra virgin olive oil
- 1 tsp flaky salt
- ½ tsp black pepper
- 1 tbsp balsamic glaze (optional)

=== Method

+ Spread arugula across the platter as the base.
+ Alternate mozzarella and tomato slices over arugula. Tuck basil between slices.
+ Right before serving, drizzle with olive oil. Season with flaky salt and pepper. Add balsamic glaze if using.

_Don't dress ahead --- tomatoes weep and arugula wilts._

---

== Melanzane pizza with pesto

_Serves 4_

=== Dough (from your meal prep recipe)

- 630 g bread flour
- 15 g sugar
- 10 g kosher salt
- 10 g instant yeast
- 32 g oil
- 420 g lukewarm water

_Makes 8 portions (~142 g each). Freeze individually; thaw in fridge overnight before use. Use 1 portion per pizza._

=== Toppings (per pizza)

- 1 eggplant (melanzane), sliced into ¼-inch rounds
- 1 tsp salt (for sweating)
- 2 tbsp olive oil (for roasting)
- 150 g fresh mozzarella, torn
- 30 g parmesan, grated
- 4 tbsp store-bought pesto

=== Method

+ *Night before:* Combine all dry dough ingredients. Add oil and water, mix until shaggy. Knead until dough passes the windowpane test (~10 min by hand). Divide into 8 balls (~142 g each), place in oiled containers, ferment in fridge 24--72 hours. Freeze unused portions.
+ *Day-of:* Lay eggplant in a single layer, sprinkle with salt, rest 30 minutes. Pat completely dry.
+ Brush slices with olive oil. Roast at 425°F (220°C) for 20--25 min, flipping halfway.
+ Place pizza stone or steel on top rack. Preheat oven to maximum (500--550°F) for at least 45 minutes.
+ Pull dough 1 hour before baking. Stretch by hand to a 12-inch round --- no rolling pin.
+ Transfer to floured peel or parchment. Top with mozzarella, parmesan, then eggplant. Bake 8--10 minutes until blistered and charred in spots.
+ Remove from oven. Spoon pesto over immediately. Slice and serve.

_Pesto goes on after baking --- heat destroys basil._

